baseline.comment:
The beach at Mon Choisy is eroding; 
Riviere des Galets is exposed to storm surges; 
Buildings in Quatre Soeurs frequently flood during high tides.

Public agencies are unclear on their obligations and current policies and regulations are inconsistent with regard to management of climate change effects in the coastal zone.

Private sector and general public do not know what options there are for coastal adaptation, nor how to initiate such measures in the most practical, cost-effective manner.
